  internet:{
    title:'How the Internet Works', readTime:'8 min',
    chunks:[
      {type:'intro', heading:'🌐 What is the Internet?',
       text:`The <span class="key-word" data-def="A massive global network connecting billions of computers and devices so they can share information">internet</span> is a worldwide network connecting billions of computers. It was created in the 1980s by scientists who needed to share research quickly. It is NOT the same as the <span class="key-word" data-def="The World Wide Web — a system of web pages and links that uses the internet">World Wide Web</span>.`,
       visual:{icon:'🌐🔗💻🌍', caption:'The internet connects billions of devices across every continent'}},
      {type:'key', heading:'📦 How Data Travels',
       text:`Information on the internet is broken into small chunks called <span class="key-word" data-def="Small pieces of data sent across a network — each packet finds its own route and they reassemble at the destination">packets</span>. These travel through cables, wi-fi signals, and satellites. Special computers called <span class="key-word" data-def="A device that directs packets of data along the fastest route through a network">routers</span> direct each packet.`,
       note:'⚡ Data travels through fibre optic cables at nearly the speed of light!'},
      {type:'visual', heading:'🔒 How Websites Work',
       text:`Websites are stored on <span class="key-word" data-def="Powerful computers that store websites and send them to users when requested">servers</span>. When you type a web address, your computer sends a request, the server sends back the <span class="key-word" data-def="Hypertext Markup Language — the code that structures every web page">HTML</span> page, and your browser displays it.`,
       visual:{icon:'💻→🌐→🖥️', caption:'Your request → travels the internet → reaches server → page returns to you'}},
      {type:'text', heading:'🔐 Internet Safety',
       text:`Stay safe online: use strong <span class="key-word" data-def="A secret combination of letters, numbers and symbols used to access an account">passwords</span>, never share personal information with strangers, look for <span class="key-word" data-def="A padlock icon and https:// showing a website has security encryption">HTTPS</span> on websites, and be aware of <span class="key-word" data-def="Fake emails or websites trying to steal your personal information">phishing</span> scams.`}
    ],
    flashcards:[
      {front:'What is the internet?', back:'A global network connecting billions of computers and devices to share information.'},
      {front:'What are packets?', back:'Small chunks of data that travel the internet separately and reassemble at the destination.'},
      {front:'What is a server?', back:'A powerful computer that stores websites and sends them to your browser when requested.'},
      {front:'What is HTTPS?', back:'A secure web protocol — the padlock icon shows the connection is encrypted and safe.'},
      {front:'What is phishing?', back:'A scam using fake emails or websites to trick you into giving personal information.'}
    ],
    quiz:[
      {q:'What is the internet?',
       options:['A type of computer','A single powerful server','A global network connecting billions of devices','Only web pages and emails'],
