  climate:{
    title:'Climate & Weather', readTime:'7 min',
    chunks:[
      {type:'intro', heading:'🌤️ Weather vs Climate',
       text:`<span class="key-word" data-def="The day-to-day atmospheric conditions in a place — rain, sun, temperature, wind">Weather</span> is what happens outside today. <span class="key-word" data-def="The average weather patterns of a region over 30+ years">Climate</span> is the long-term pattern. A simple memory trick: "Climate is what you expect, weather is what you get."`,
       visual:{icon:'☀️🌧️❄️🌪️', caption:'Weather changes daily — climate is the overall pattern over decades'}},
      {type:'key', heading:'🌡️ Climate Zones',
       text:`Earth has major <span class="key-word" data-def="Bands around Earth with similar climate patterns based on distance from the equator">climate zones</span>: <span class="key-word" data-def="The hot, wet zone near the equator — rainforests and jungles">Tropical</span> (hot & wet), <span class="key-word" data-def="The dry zone between tropical and temperate — includes most deserts">Arid/Desert</span>, <span class="key-word" data-def="Moderate zone with four seasons — most of Europe and USA">Temperate</span> (four seasons), and <span class="key-word" data-def="The cold zones near the poles — permanently frozen">Polar</span> (freezing).`,
       note:'🌡️ The hottest recorded temperature was 56.7°C in Death Valley, USA!'},
      {type:'visual', heading:'🌊 Climate Change',
       text:`<span class="key-word" data-def="The long-term shift in global temperatures and weather patterns, mainly caused by human activities burning fossil fuels">Climate change</span> refers to global warming caused by <span class="key-word" data-def="Gases like CO₂ and methane that trap heat in Earth's atmosphere">greenhouse gases</span>. The Earth's average temperature has risen about 1.1°C since the Industrial Revolution.`,
       visual:{icon:'🌡️📈🌍', caption:'Global average temperatures have been rising since industrialisation'}},
      {type:'text', heading:'🌬️ What Causes Weather?',
       text:`Weather is caused by <span class="key-word" data-def="A large mass of air with similar temperature and humidity, covering thousands of kilometres">air masses</span> moving around Earth. When warm and cold air masses meet, they create <span class="key-word" data-def="The boundary between two air masses with different temperatures — causes rain, wind and storms">fronts</span> which cause rain and storms.`}
    ],
    flashcards:[
      {front:'Difference between weather and climate?', back:'Weather = today\'s conditions. Climate = average pattern over 30+ years.'},
      {front:'Name 4 climate zones', back:'Tropical (hot/wet), Arid/Desert (dry), Temperate (4 seasons), Polar (freezing).'},
      {front:'What causes climate change?', back:'Burning fossil fuels releases greenhouse gases (CO₂, methane) that trap heat in the atmosphere.'},
      {front:'What is a weather front?', back:'A boundary between warm and cold air masses — usually causes rain, wind and storms.'},
      {front:'Which climate zone has 4 seasons?', back:'Temperate zones — like most of Europe, USA, China — have spring, summer, autumn and winter.'}
    ],
    quiz:[
